{
  "stem": "15721.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because a big, black dog came and scared the hell out of me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it-- if it hadn't been for a man who came by who called the dog off or chased him away, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I would have died of fright.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So that was just about then the end.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because Mother then realized that unless she had help, which then eventually we a maid, a live-in maid soon thereafter.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But also, not long after that, my second brother arrived.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And that kind of ended my mother's academic career.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But it is indicative of the fact that she came from an intellectual family, an Eastern European family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Both her brothers were physicians, one a surgeon and the other one an ophthalmologist.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she, she was a very competent lady.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Among her really notable achievements was the fact that despite the fact that she was really Eastern European, and in Germany there was a tremendous conflict, you might almost say, between the true German Jews and those who had eastern descent or origins.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, the German Jews were really not secure enough not to be scared by the influx of Eastern European Jewry who spoke Yiddish, which is distorted German, who had these peculiar, quaint customs, and who didn't quite dress like everybody else, and who simply were the poor relatives.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And German Jews had just clawed their way into some form of, of equality.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was, I think, illusory to begin with.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But not everybody realized that.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In fact, they fought hard to become recognized and accepted citizens of, of Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this, they felt-- perhaps not unjustifiably, actually-- that Eastern European Jews were a threat to their very fragile standing.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
